1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,400
<i>We've got a situation!</i>

2
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:08,000
If Pae is dead, that's good.
That's one less enemy for me.

3
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,320
I will appoint you

4
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:12,120
<i>as head of the railway construction unit.</i>

5
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,200
Yiam!

6
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:15,920
<i>Even if it costs me my life,</i>
<i>I have to stop them.</i>

7
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:17,680
<i>Aren't you afraid</i>
<i>of being charged with rebellion?</i>

8
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,920
What is going on?

9
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,280
How can I destroy
the Lek Lai inside Yiam, Dad?

10
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,560
A woman's menstrual blood.

11
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:25,920
<i>A woman's menstrual blood carries a curse.</i>
<i>No matter how powerful the sorcery may be,</i>

12
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,840
<i>it will deteriorate.</i>

13
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:31,000
I won't use Lek Lai to harm your brother

14
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:33,040
if he stops doing evil,

15
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,240
turns himself in.

16
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,080
You're being used as a pawn.

17
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,840
Where are you leaving me to go?

18
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,720
I just have some business in another town.

19
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:52,680
What business?

20
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,880
Master, there's no way
to defeat him at all?

21
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,800
There is.

22
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:06,360
If you eat the flesh
of Old Master Khrua Phut,

23
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:07,920
the head of Khao Phrom,

24
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:11,360
the sorcery inside you

25
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,480
will grow a hundredfold, a thousandfold.

26
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,560
I have to eat human flesh?

27
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,160
Yes.

28
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:28,120
Fresh flesh from Old Master Khrua Phut

29
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:31,680
is more powerful than
any sacred item in the world.

30
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,840
If you eat it,

31
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,960
Old Master Khrua Phut's sorcery

32
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:45,080
will live in your body, in your blood,

33
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,200
and in your soul.

34
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,880
Nothing can resist it.

35
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,480
Not even Yiam's

36
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,520
Klaikot Lek Lai.

37
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:00,360
It's the governor's business.

38
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,520
It's nothing.

39
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,960
I'll be back.

40
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,880
Can I come with you?

41
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,640
I don't want to stay here alone.

42
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:20,120
I just lost my father and my sister,

43
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,440
and then Tim too.

44
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,320
I'm scared.

45
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,240
I'm scared I'll be next.

46
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:34,040
My lady,

47
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:36,920
don't be afraid.

48
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:39,280
While I'm gone,

49
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,120
I'll find someone to protect you.

50
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,520
His name is Nui.

51
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:53,920
He's my cousin.

52
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,040
You can trust him.

53
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:59,520
I'll have him stay with you at night,

54
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,360
so you won't be afraid.

55
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,560
While I'm gone, take care of Lady Duen.

56
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,200
Sure.

57
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:27,320
I'll keep my eyes on Lady Duen,
every second.

58
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,080
Nui.

59
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,800
Lady Duen is my woman.
Don't get too greedy.

60
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:39,640
Lasor, I wouldn't dare
do anything beyond your orders.

61
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,600
And about Tim's death,

62
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:46,640
the one who killed him

63
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:50,560
is probably someone with powerful sorcery.
If you hear anything,

64
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,120
you report to me immediately.

65
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,640
Sure.

66
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,160
Lasor,

67
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,480
you won't change your mind, right?
About Old Master Khrua Phut?

68
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:05,960
Master said

69
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,960
if I eat Old Master Khrua Phut's
fresh flesh,

70
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,080
I'll become the lord of dark magic.

71
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,640
Then I won't have to suffer

72
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:18,000
from the curse that eats away at me
every new-moon night.

73
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,800
But Old Master Khrua Phut's sorcery

74
00:06:21,880 --> 00:06:23,320
is powerful.

75
00:06:24,280 --> 00:06:26,120
You've seen it with your own eyes.

76
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:30,200
But today isn't like back then.

77
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,520
Master has taught me
every last bit of dark magic.

78
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:37,440
Old Master Khrua Phut's white magic
can't do anything to me.

79
00:07:03,080 --> 00:07:04,200
<i>Don't worry.</i>

80
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,480
<i>I won't use Lek Lai to harm your brother</i>

81
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:11,480
<i>if he stops doing evil,</i>

82
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,240
<i>turns himself in,</i>

83
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:16,000
<i>and confesses everything.</i>

84
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,919
Be careful.

85
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,840
My special gunpowder
can blow mountains to pieces.

86
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,960
Where did you get these recipes?

87
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:55,120
When I studied at Khao Phrom,

88
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,320
I once read formulas
for mixing gunpowder and elements

89
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,520
in a military strategy text.

90
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:04,320
Ancient Indians knew how to make
gunpowder thousands of years ago.

91
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:06,040
So I memorized it and put it to use.

92
00:09:08,040 --> 00:09:09,920
In China, there's a similar formula.

93
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:12,720
Saltpeter from bat guano, sulfur,

94
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,400
and charcoal.

95
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:17,880
I think I'll try mixing
my own version too.

96
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,040
Good.

97
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,840
Mix Yiam's formula with yours.

98
00:09:24,160 --> 00:09:25,600
Phraya Kaipetch's railway

99
00:09:25,680 --> 00:09:27,120
is gonna go up in flames for sure.

100
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:34,520
Pun.

101
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,120
What's wrong with you?

102
00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:49,280
If you've got something to say,
say it straight. You're my friend.

103
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,040
It's because you're my friend.

104
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,160
That's why I don't want you
doing crazy things like this.

105
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:01,480
A man's born once, dies once.

106
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,840
Are you scared to die, Pun?

107
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,520
All my life,
I've never been afraid to die.

108
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:10,280
But this is too risky.

109
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,080
Yiam,

110
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,200
if we fail,

111
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:19,040
all of us will be charged as rebels.

112
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:23,920
I don't want someone who has nothing
to do with this, like Noree,

113
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,360
to get dragged down with us too.

114
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:31,120
So you don't want to get involved because

115
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:33,440
you're worried about Noree?

116
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,840
I don't want Noree to end up like my Dad.

117
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:49,000
I understand you, Pun.

118
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,920
But I really don't have a choice.

119
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,880
I have to do this.

120
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:30,240
You stay here. Don't come with us.

121
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:34,120
I'm afraid
you'll get dragged into trouble too.

122
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:36,800
I'm already wanted

123
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,680
for killing Phraya Decha,
the former governor.

124
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:43,600
So what if I get charged as a rebel too?

125
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:49,040
I'm your wife, Yiam.

126
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:52,640
Where the husband goes,

127
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,400
the wife goes.

128
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,640
Thank you, Yiwha.

129
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:44,400
<i>Phutthakaro tatiyachanang.</i>

130
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,640
<i>Thakaro chatutthangchanang.</i>

131
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:50,160
<i>Chatari namo buddhaya latthanang.</i>

132
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,160
Old Master Khrua Phut! Stop!

133
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:52,800
Old Master!

134
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:59,400
I told you to stop. You wanna test me?

135
00:14:00,120 --> 00:14:01,120
Fine.

136
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,600
The governor has ordered

137
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:06,960
the police to deploy strict security

138
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,120
around the railway construction site,

139
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:13,440
especially this mountain pass area.

140
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:16,120
That black-masked guy
will definitely strike again soon, sir.

141
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:19,200
Do you know who he is, to be so audacious?

142
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,640
It's Yiam,

143
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,640
Khun Yod Pakdee's son, sir.

144
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:25,200
That's just baseless rumors.

145
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:28,000
Everyone knows Yiam is dead.

146
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:31,800
Sir Lasor, the railway foreman,

147
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:32,880
said it himself.

148
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:33,960
Enough.

149
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:37,160
Whoever that black-masked man is,

150
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,920
there are laws and order in this land.

151
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:42,600
Sabotaging the railway is rebellion.

152
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:45,880
We must capture him
and punish him as soon as possible.

153
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,360
Your old boss has barely died,

154
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:01,120
and you've already got a new one.

155
00:15:02,040 --> 00:15:03,320
You change colors fast.

156
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:06,400
Only people who know how to adapt survive.

157
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,240
You should too.

158
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:12,160
If you want to rise higher, come join me.

159
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,840
Join you? For what?

160
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,840
Capture Yiam
and deliver him to the governor.

161
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,800
And I'll put in a good word for you.

162
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:28,080
If you make an enemy of Phraya Kaipetch,

163
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,680
you're just rushing to your own death.

164
00:15:31,240 --> 00:15:34,240
But if you help me crush the rebels,

165
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:36,480
and bring Yiam in for punishment,

166
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,400
you'll live comfortably
for the rest of your life.

167
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:44,240
Think carefully, Pun.

168
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:14,680
I've made my decision.
I'm going to help Yiam.

169
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:20,080
Aren't you afraid
of getting arrested for rebellion?

170
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,680
I have to repay this land
for giving me a place to live.

171
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,160
I'm going too.

172
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:43,280
Why? It's dangerous.

173
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:47,360
I'm going to help you and Yiam

174
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,720
fight those evil bastards
trying to sell out the country.

175
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,800
Even if I stop you,

176
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:59,680
you'd just sneak after me anyway, right?

177
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,440
Pa,

178
00:17:14,599 --> 00:17:16,560
please protect me

179
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,240
and Chang.

180
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:26,440
Don't worry, sir.

181
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:29,040
I swear I'll protect Talong with my life.

182
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:34,600
You just made a promise to my dad.

183
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,800
I'm promising you too, Talong.

184
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,760
If we can blow
that section of the pass down,

185
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:55,680
they won't be able
to build the railway anymore.

186
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,000
But the police have troops everywhere.

187
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:04,240
How will you break through?

188
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,120
We have to lure them elsewhere.

189
00:18:16,760 --> 00:18:17,960
Then I'll go myself.

190
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,080
Are you sure, Yiwha?

191
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,800
While Yiwha lures the police away,

192
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,640
you, me, and Talong

193
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:36,120
will rush in and plant bombs
at the key points,

194
00:18:36,200 --> 00:18:37,360
no time wasted.

195
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:39,840
Once we're ready, we blow it.

196
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,160
Yiam,

197
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:45,040
my special gunpowder bombs

198
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:46,760
are not gonna lose to yours.

199
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:52,920
Thank you, both of you,
for risking your lives with me.

200
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,120
I'll never forget it.

201
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,040
- Hey! Get her!
- Let's go!

202
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,360
Hey! Stop!

203
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,000
Go! Now!

204
00:20:31,120 --> 00:20:32,160
You guys.

205
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:33,840
Pun.

206
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,720
Go! Let's go now.

207
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:41,560
Yiam, your recklessness
is going to get other people in trouble.

208
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:45,120
This has nothing to do with anyone else.
I'll take full responsibility myself.

209
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,640
Catch those rebels!

210
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,920
Over there! The rebels ran that way!

211
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,120
Your Excellency.

212
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:08,440
Go fetch Luang Kamchat Phairi,
your commander, here now.

213
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:09,560
Yes, sir.

214
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:17,680
When we bombed the mountain,

215
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:21,240
I saw someone standing
on the water, staring at me,

216
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:28,000
before transforming
into a black crow and flying away.

217
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,400
A crow?

218
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:34,280
Could it be the one who killed Duang?

219
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:38,120
What do you mean, Chang?

220
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,360
<i>Pun told me,</i>

221
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:46,520
<i>when he examined Duang's body,</i>

222
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:50,240
there was
a black crow feather at the scene.

223
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,680
Do you remember what he looked like, Yiam?

224
00:21:54,400 --> 00:21:55,520
I couldn't see his face clearly.

225
00:21:58,280 --> 00:21:59,880
Someone who can turn into a crow

226
00:22:01,400 --> 00:22:03,480
has to be a sorcerer.

227
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:08,040
It might be the one
who tore out Duang's heart,

228
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:10,760
and the mastermind behind everything.

229
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:20,000
Now Petch has become the new governor
of Tha Khiri, replacing Duang.

230
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,760
After I drove Lasor out of Chum Suea,

231
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:25,560
he likely went to study
dark sorcery under Petch.

232
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,680
That's why he calls him Master.

233
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,120
I remember now.

234
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:32,720
My dad once said that

235
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:34,160
Phraya Kaipetch

236
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:36,080
studied at Khao Phrom together with him.

237
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,560
Lasor must have learned sorcery from him.

238
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:42,040
That's why he calls
Phraya Kaipetch his master.

239
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:47,320
I need to know exactly

240
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:50,240
who Phraya Kaipetch really is.

241
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,600
Thanks, Pun, for today.

242
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:10,120
I didn't help you.

243
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,120
I helped Chang,

244
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,800
Talong, and Yiwha,

245
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,280
so they wouldn't be in trouble
because of you.

246
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:24,120
I never wanted
to drag anyone into trouble.

247
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:27,640
Everyone chose to act for what's right.

248
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,960
You still dare call this "right," Yiam?

249
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:38,240
Rebellion. Destroying state property.

250
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,560
Creating unrest.

251
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,560
Everything you've done is illegal,

252
00:23:42,440 --> 00:23:43,880
punishable by death.

253
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:46,720
When power is in the hands of evil men,
only disaster follows.

254
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,080
Black becomes white.

255
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,000
Wrong becomes right.

256
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:53,080
If I do nothing,

257
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:56,200
countless innocent people will suffer.

258
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:58,480
Who do you think you are? God?

259
00:23:58,560 --> 00:23:59,680
Huh, Yiam?

260
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:03,360
Kaipetch's power reaches
the sky and the earth.

261
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,920
And who are you?

262
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:06,680
What can you do by yourself?

263
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,640
Give it up, Yiam,

264
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:13,160
before everything is completely destroyed.

265
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,440
I know you're worried about me.

266
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:18,000
But I can't stand watching people suffer

267
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:20,240
under that bastard of a governor.

268
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,120
Yiam.

269
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:27,960
You'll regret this.

270
00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,480
Does Old Master Khrua Phut
have any weakness?

271
00:25:05,440 --> 00:25:07,160
Every sorcerer

272
00:25:08,160 --> 00:25:09,800
has a day of loss,

273
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:14,400
a day when their powers weaken,

274
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:16,640
almost like an ordinary man.

275
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,760
The upcoming waning-moon fifteenth night

276
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,800
is Old Master Phut's day of loss.

277
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:30,600
Wait until the bandit star

278
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:32,600
shines bright in the sky,

279
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,080
then strike.

280
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:39,440
<i>At that moment, Old Master Khrua Phut</i>

281
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:43,640
will be like a chicken in your grasp.

282
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,120
Your fate hasn't reached its end yet.

283
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:50,640
Wait until the bandit star ascends.

284
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:52,600
You won't escape me.

285
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:26,880
Yiwha?

286
00:26:45,160 --> 00:26:46,200
Can't sleep?

287
00:26:51,360 --> 00:26:54,120
Now that the railway's
been blown to pieces,

288
00:26:55,520 --> 00:26:57,000
what are you going to do next?

289
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:06,280
I guess…

290
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:10,920
I'll track down your father
and your brother

291
00:27:13,280 --> 00:27:16,720
and turn them over to
the Provincial Patrol Department.

292
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:25,560
Don't forget.

293
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:28,920
My father and brother are bandits.

294
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,200
Handing them over to the authorities

295
00:27:32,280 --> 00:27:34,200
is the same as sending them
to their deaths.

296
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:44,400
Didn't you promise me

297
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,720
you'd find evidence to prove it?

298
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:52,840
What evidence is there left to find?

299
00:27:53,400 --> 00:27:56,000
Everyone who knew the truth is dead.

300
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:59,680
This is the only way
to uncover what really happened.

301
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:44,000
Old Master Khrua Phut,
with your powerful clairvoyance,

302
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:48,360
you must already know why I've come.

303
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:53,160
The wrong view that binds you

304
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:55,680
will drag your life into ruin,

305
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,120
sinking you endlessly into suffering.

306
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:02,800
Even in death, a lower realm awaits you.

307
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:06,120
Abandon this intention

308
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:07,440
and turn back.

309
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:12,720
Old Master,

310
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,880
are you afraid of death too?

311
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:20,360
All beings must eventually perish.

312
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:22,000
Why fear death?

313
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:25,880
The body is nothing
more than a decaying vessel.

314
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,080
Good.

315
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,680
If you don't fear death,

316
00:29:31,720 --> 00:29:33,560
then give your life to me.

317
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:37,440
I am here.

318
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:40,480
If you want my life,

319
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,560
then come and take it.

320
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:46,080
<i>Yathapi kumbhakarassa</i>

321
00:29:46,160 --> 00:29:48,560
<i>yathapi kumbhakarassa</i>

322
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:50,960
<i>kata mattikabhajana</i>

323
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:53,560
<i>sabbe bheda-pariyanta</i>

324
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:56,280
<i>evang maccana jivitang.</i>

325
00:29:57,120 --> 00:29:59,640
Just as all clay vessels made by a potter

326
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:02,400
are destined to break,

327
00:30:03,200 --> 00:30:05,840
so too are the lives of all beings.

328
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,040
Old Master.

329
00:30:16,160 --> 00:30:18,720
Save your sermon for the next life.

330
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,480
Phraya Kaipetch
must be losing his mind now

331
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:33,520
that the railway tunnel's
been blown to pieces.

332
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,680
They won't take an attack lying down.

333
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:40,200
I'm sure they're already
preparing to strike back.

334
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:43,080
Let them come. I'm not afraid.

335
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:47,960
Don't underestimate him.
This Phraya Kaipetch

336
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:50,360
is a sorcerer.

337
00:30:50,440 --> 00:30:52,880
He could be planning
something we'd never expect.

338
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:00,040
What are you afraid of? We've got Yiam.

339
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:11,400
Yiam this and Yiam that.

340
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:14,680
I really wonder

341
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,680
if I ever exist in your head at all.

342
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:23,880
Talong,

343
00:31:25,800 --> 00:31:27,120
are you sulking?

344
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:32,000
I'm not.

345
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:35,160
I don't believe you.

346
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,560
Your eyes give you away.

347
00:31:46,120 --> 00:31:49,200
And didn't my eyes tell you

348
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,560
how I feel?

349
00:32:36,800 --> 00:32:38,600
The mighty master of Khao Phrom,

350
00:32:39,280 --> 00:32:40,840
the powerful sorcerer,

351
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:45,560
in the end, he's nothing more than
what's in Lasor's stomach now.

352
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:51,400
Master.

353
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:55,440
I'm the lord
of dark sorcery now, aren't I?

354
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:59,760
Of course you are.

355
00:33:02,760 --> 00:33:05,520
But I truly admire you,

356
00:33:06,080 --> 00:33:09,240
killing even a monk without hesitation.

357
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:13,360
I thought I was evil.
Turns out I'm not as bad as you.

358
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,520
Then now, I can kill Yiam, right?

359
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:26,120
You could kill him anytime.

360
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:29,840
- But I won't allow it yet.
- Why not, Master?

361
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:33,440
Because I want to
tear out his heart and eat it

362
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:36,240
while he's still alive.

363
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:40,640
Only then will it be fitting punishment

364
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:43,120
for daring to blow up my railway.

365
00:33:52,520 --> 00:33:54,280
Yiam!

366
00:33:57,440 --> 00:34:00,880
Yiam, you and I
can't live in the same world.

367
00:34:03,360 --> 00:34:04,960
That's exactly how it should be, Lasor.

368
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:32,360
What do you say, Mun?

369
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:35,639
Will you take me to the capital or not?

370
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:38,480
Yes, my lady.
Tonight, at the second watch,

371
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:41,639
wait for me at the back of the house.
I'll have the wagon ready.

372
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:56,159
Let's go, my lady.

373
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:00,040
Where are you going?

374
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:03,360
Where I go is none of your business.

375
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,760
Come on, Mun.

376
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:10,040
You should go back to bed, my lady.

377
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:14,120
They say this place is haunted.

378
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,560
Hey, I've lived here for years

379
00:35:20,640 --> 00:35:22,120
and never seen a single ghost.

380
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:25,360
If they're real, let them show themselves.

381
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:33,640
You really want to see a ghost?

382
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:40,440
G… Ghost!

383
00:35:40,520 --> 00:35:41,600
Hey! Mun!

384
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:42,880
- Ghost!
- Mun!

385
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,320
Where are you going?!

386
00:35:44,400 --> 00:35:46,920
Mun is gone. Looks like

387
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:50,440
you won't be going anywhere tonight.

388
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:54,960
Whoa!

389
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:05,560
PATROL UNIT

390
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:08,600
The governor has ordered you
suspended from duty indefinitely.

391
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:11,600
Why, sir?

392
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,360
You still have the nerve to ask?

393
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:15,920
You let those rebels get away.

394
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,000
You should be grateful
I'm not throwing you in jail

395
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,240
for conspiring with them.

396
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:23,720
Then what about the other cases
I've been handling, sir?

397
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:28,640
Starting today, you are not to
involve yourself in any case at all.

398
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,800
I'll assign someone else to take over.

399
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,520
Take care, my friend.

400
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:57,600
And I'll be watching

401
00:36:58,320 --> 00:37:00,640
to see how
a two-faced dog like you ends up.

402
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:23,000
Pun, you're not on duty today?

403
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:26,920
No.

404
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:30,640
I don't have to work
at the police unit anymore.

405
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,840
Oh? Why?

406
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:36,040
I've been suspended indefinitely.

407
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:39,240
But maybe it's for the best.

408
00:37:40,440 --> 00:37:42,120
No more work chaos.

409
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,880
I'll finally have time for myself.

410
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:50,120
Is something bothering you?

411
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,400
You can tell me, you know.

412
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:54,440
It's nothing.

413
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:56,840
I'd rather help you wash.

414
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,360
- Wash?
- Mhm.

415
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:03,400
Oh.

416
00:38:03,920 --> 00:38:05,600
Pun.

417
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:09,480
Pun, easy, easy. The fabric will tear.

418
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,160
Gently.

419
00:38:11,240 --> 00:38:12,320
I'll teach you.

420
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:13,760
- Alright.
- Be gentle.

421
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,040
Like this.

422
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:18,080
Alright.

423
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:23,160
- Wash gently.
- Okay.

424
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:30,440
Everyone has disappeared,
Uncle Niem, Uncle Chaem,

425
00:38:30,520 --> 00:38:34,200
Chang, Yiwha.
I'm the only one left at home.

426
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:39,840
Pun, do you know where they went?

427
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,720
I don't know either.

428
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:45,760
Just dealing with my own mess
is giving me a headache.

429
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:50,600
Then what will you do next?

430
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:53,400
I'll find other work.

431
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:56,040
Or maybe open a shop like my dad did.

432
00:38:57,320 --> 00:39:00,240
You're smart. You can do anything.

433
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:03,200
Later, I'll help you clean
and take care of the shop.

434
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,320
Thank you, Noree.

435
00:39:05,920 --> 00:39:07,920
If you weren't here,
taking care of the house,

436
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:10,640
the meals, everything, I'd be done for.

437
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:14,560
I'm useless. I can't do anything right.

438
00:39:15,680 --> 00:39:17,720
Pun, you were a policeman.

439
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:20,600
Helping people, keeping the town safe,
that's already good enough.

440
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:23,600
As for housework, let that be my job.

441
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:25,800
Don't overthink it.

442
00:39:27,320 --> 00:39:28,200
- Okay.
- Alright.

443
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:29,840
From now on,

444
00:39:30,880 --> 00:39:32,920
I'll have more time for you.

445
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:56,720
Have you seen this yet?

446
00:39:56,800 --> 00:40:00,360
"Wanted. The Masked Man and his rebel gang
who bombed the railway. Death sentence."

447
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:07,320
WANTED: THE MASKED MAN
AND HIS REBEL GANG WHO BOMBED THE RAILWAY.

448
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:09,720
DEATH SENTENCE.

449
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:12,840
You're so cool.
We're cool by association too.

450
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:18,960
How is being sentenced to death cool?

451
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:22,560
The villagers are praising
the masked man's group,

452
00:40:22,640 --> 00:40:25,920
for saving the country from those thug
officials trying to sell the nation out.

453
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,560
Right now, the masked man
is the hottest outlaw.

454
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:32,360
Widows and aunties from Khuan Phra Ngam

455
00:40:32,440 --> 00:40:34,680
to Tha Khiri to Huai Yao

456
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:36,440
are dying to know

457
00:40:36,520 --> 00:40:39,440
what the black-masked hero looks like.

458
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:44,360
Just don't let anyone find out
you're working with me.

459
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,600
Or you'll get charged with rebellion too.

460
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:48,600
Alright.

461
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,120
Oh.

462
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:56,520
Have you heard about Pun?
He got suspended by his boss.

463
00:41:10,440 --> 00:41:11,600
Yiam.

464
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:16,280
I'll go get the vegetables.

465
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,360
Alright.

466
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,640
I'm sorry for getting you into trouble.

467
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:28,000
So you can feel sorry

468
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,040
that other people suffer
the consequences of what you do?

469
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,600
You can curse me all you want.

470
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,560
I'll take all the blame.

471
00:41:38,560 --> 00:41:39,920
Cursing you won't change anything.

472
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:43,720
People like you don't cry
until you see the coffin.

473
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:11,440
What's wrong, Yiam?

474
00:42:12,040 --> 00:42:13,880
You don't look well.

475
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:19,160
My impulsiveness

476
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:23,760
wrecked everyone's lives.

477
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:29,120
Everyone around me
is now hanging by a thread.

478
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,680
Phraya Kaipetch won't let this go.

479
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:46,480
Everyone makes mistakes.

480
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:51,280
But we can turn mistakes into lessons.

481
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:54,360
You meant well.

482
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:58,880
You wanted to help the villagers
and to keep Tha Khiri safe.

483
00:42:59,920 --> 00:43:03,880
It's just that your method
might've been a little too rash.

484
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:08,040
Next time,
you just need to be more careful.

485
00:43:24,880 --> 00:43:26,120
I have something for you.

486
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:28,800
What is it?

487
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:31,800
A sarong.

488
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:34,120
You'll look beautiful wearing it.

489
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:38,800
I'll hold this for you.

490
00:43:49,080 --> 00:43:50,600
If none of this had happened,

491
00:43:52,480 --> 00:43:54,680
we could've been so happy, right, Yiwha?

492
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:05,440
We can't run from the truth.

493
00:44:06,600 --> 00:44:08,320
But since it already happened,

494
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:11,000
we can still be happy.

495
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:13,480
If you…

496
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:16,560
let go.

497
00:45:44,520 --> 00:45:46,400
We can't turn back time,

498
00:45:47,600 --> 00:45:51,240
but I'll make you go back
to being that same old Blur again.

499
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:14,040
Mun! When are you
taking me to the capital, Mun?

500
00:46:14,120 --> 00:46:15,920
Come out and talk to me.

501
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:17,680
I already paid you.

502
00:46:17,760 --> 00:46:20,360
Are you trying to cheat me, huh?

503
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:22,160
Mun!

504
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:27,560
Help! Help!

505
00:46:27,640 --> 00:46:29,800
My lady. It's me.

506
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:32,600
- Lasor.
- What happened?

507
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:36,560
This was your doing, wasn't it?

508
00:46:38,800 --> 00:46:41,120
Mun was going to help Lady Duen
escape to the capital.

509
00:46:41,880 --> 00:46:43,440
I had no choice.

510
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:46,720
She still hasn't given up on
leaving for the capital?

511
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:51,400
She's been trying to go back
with every breath she takes.

512
00:46:54,440 --> 00:46:57,040
I've done everything right,

513
00:46:58,200 --> 00:46:59,880
yet I could never win her heart.

514
00:47:02,240 --> 00:47:03,680
I told you already.

515
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:05,760
Just finish her.

516
00:47:06,800 --> 00:47:08,040
That's it.

517
00:47:09,920 --> 00:47:13,520
Once she becomes your woman,
she'll stop resisting.

518
00:47:17,200 --> 00:47:18,120
Nui,

519
00:47:19,240 --> 00:47:20,600
is there really no other way?

520
00:47:22,480 --> 00:47:24,800
There's no faster

521
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:27,360
or more effective way than this.

522
00:47:44,880 --> 00:47:49,120
Yiam and his gang stormed in
and bombed my railway.

523
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:50,800
Everything was ruined.

524
00:47:51,840 --> 00:47:54,760
Those rebels must be wiped out.

525
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:02,240
Lasor, killing people is easy.

526
00:48:03,640 --> 00:48:07,200
But even if you kill them all,
other groups

527
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:10,920
will rise again. Rebellion will never end.

528
00:48:12,640 --> 00:48:13,640
Then

529
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:17,120
we must make an example of them.

530
00:48:17,800 --> 00:48:19,040
If they see

531
00:48:20,160 --> 00:48:21,720
what happens to rebels,

532
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:25,560
no one will dare defy you again, Master.

533
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,720
Do whatever you want, Lasor.

534
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,400
But I ask for one thing.

535
00:48:37,480 --> 00:48:38,880
Yiam must be captured alive.

536
00:48:40,400 --> 00:48:41,760
I understand, Master.

537
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:54,560
The store's closed today.
Please come back another time.

538
00:49:04,760 --> 00:49:05,640
Noree.

539
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:23,600
Noree.

540
00:49:31,080 --> 00:49:33,320
- Go!
- Let go!

541
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:36,320
Hey, why did you bring me here?

542
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:37,840
If Pun really loves you,

543
00:49:38,360 --> 00:49:40,280
he'll come with help to save you.

544
00:49:41,640 --> 00:49:43,800
Lock her up inside the residence.
Watch her closely.

545
00:49:43,880 --> 00:49:44,960
- Yes, sir.
- Let go.

546
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:47,760
- Go!
- Let go!

547
00:50:08,080 --> 00:50:12,520
Villagers say the people
from the governor's residence took Noree.

548
00:50:15,600 --> 00:50:17,040
It must be Lasor's men.

549
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:19,080
I'm going to find Noree.

550
00:50:19,680 --> 00:50:22,920
Calm down, Pun. I know you're worried,

551
00:50:23,840 --> 00:50:25,680
but use your head.

552
00:50:27,320 --> 00:50:29,960
I think Noree is being held
at the governor's residence.

553
00:50:30,560 --> 00:50:32,480
They want to force you to cooperate,

554
00:50:32,560 --> 00:50:36,200
so they can capture Yiam
and wipe all of us out.

555
00:50:36,280 --> 00:50:37,640
Bastards.

556
00:50:38,640 --> 00:50:40,440
How far are they going to push me?

557
00:50:44,320 --> 00:50:47,600
Let's find a way to help Noree first.

558
00:50:54,200 --> 00:50:56,840
<i>If you make an enemy of Phraya Kaipetch,</i>

559
00:50:57,440 --> 00:50:59,640
you're just rushing to your own death.

560
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:03,400
But if you help me crush the rebels,

561
00:51:03,480 --> 00:51:05,560
and bring Yiam in for punishment,

562
00:51:06,760 --> 00:51:08,520
you'll live comfortably
for the rest of your life.

563
00:51:33,720 --> 00:51:36,440
<i>Everyone who knew the truth is dead.</i>

564
00:51:37,200 --> 00:51:39,600
This is the only way
to uncover what really happened.

565
00:51:40,520 --> 00:51:42,440
We can't run from the truth.

566
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:45,240
But since it already happened,

567
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:47,960
we can still be happy.

568
00:51:48,560 --> 00:51:49,920
If you…

569
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:52,960
let go.

570
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:57,040
Forgive me, Yiam.

571
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:37,520
You were going to destroy
the Lek Lai inside me?

572
00:52:42,080 --> 00:52:43,320
I never thought

573
00:52:44,640 --> 00:52:48,160
the woman I love would do this to me.

574
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:53,760
I… I had to do it.

575
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,280
If I don't,

576
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:58,360
how many people will be ruined

577
00:52:58,440 --> 00:52:59,840
by your arrogance,

578
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,200
including you.
You'll die from your arrogance.

579
00:53:05,400 --> 00:53:07,480
You think you're above everyone else.

580
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:10,560
You want me to die by your father's
and brother's hands, don't you?

581
00:53:11,280 --> 00:53:13,080
I don't want anyone to die.

582
00:53:23,960 --> 00:53:25,080
From now on,

583
00:53:27,120 --> 00:53:28,560
you and I…

584
00:53:34,240 --> 00:53:35,440
are finished.

585
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:48,520
Yiam!

586
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:52,840
Sir Lasor, someone is here to see you.

587
00:55:20,840 --> 00:55:22,280
Lasor.

588
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:23,440
Yiam.

589
00:55:24,320 --> 00:55:27,480
So this is where you've been hiding,
just like Pun said.

590
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:31,640
What did you do to my friend?

591
00:55:31,720 --> 00:55:33,040
I didn't do anything.

592
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:37,280
Pun came to me on his own. He sold you out

593
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:40,840
in exchange for a position
in the police force that I promised him.

594
00:55:41,920 --> 00:55:43,760
I don't believe you, you bastard.

595
00:55:46,760 --> 00:55:49,160
There's a lot more you still don't know,

596
00:55:49,960 --> 00:55:51,000
you little bastard.

597
00:56:05,600 --> 00:56:06,600
The Lek Lai inside you,

598
00:56:06,680 --> 00:56:08,320
is that all it can do?

599
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:26,200
Even if blades can't pierce you,

600
00:56:30,320 --> 00:56:32,600
I still have ways to kill you, Yiam.

601
00:56:43,480 --> 00:56:47,280
I'm enjoying this.
Don't you dare die too easily on me.

602
00:56:49,320 --> 00:56:50,640
Come on. What have you got?

603
00:56:53,600 --> 00:56:56,320
Listen to me. Your master's flesh

604
00:56:56,400 --> 00:56:57,640
really is as powerful

605
00:56:59,440 --> 00:57:01,680
as Master Kaipetch said.

606
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:04,840
What did you do to Old Master Khrua Phut?

607
00:57:08,880 --> 00:57:11,720
That's impossible.
Old Master has powerful sorcery.

608
00:57:12,360 --> 00:57:14,000
He'd never lose to a bastard like you!

609
00:57:18,840 --> 00:57:20,720
- Ugh!
- Then go ask him in hell.

610
00:57:20,800 --> 00:57:22,000
Die!

611
00:57:24,120 --> 00:57:26,000
Pun betrayed his friend

612
00:57:26,080 --> 00:57:27,240
just to save your life.

613
00:57:27,320 --> 00:57:29,120
What have you done, Pun?

614
00:57:29,200 --> 00:57:31,000
You'll die just like you want to.

615
00:57:32,080 --> 00:57:33,040
<i>I almost killed Yiam,</i>

616
00:57:33,640 --> 00:57:34,920
but someone with sorcery saved him.

617
00:57:35,000 --> 00:57:38,280
I've found the evidence
to expose Phraya Kaipetch.

618
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:41,680
<i>I have three dangerous criminals</i>
<i>for you to punish.</i>

619
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:43,560
Dad!

620
00:57:47,400 --> 00:57:49,160
Where are your rebel friends hiding?

621
00:57:49,240 --> 00:57:50,240
Lasor!

622
00:57:52,440 --> 00:57:53,280
- Yiwha.
- Yiwha.

623
00:57:53,360 --> 00:57:55,560
<i>No matter how much medicine you take,</i>
<i>you still won't wake up.</i>

624
00:57:56,160 --> 00:57:58,360
I have to find a way to save you, Yiwha.

625
00:57:59,280 --> 00:58:02,000
But what if we can't find the Twin Lotus

626
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:03,360
or don't make it back in time?

627
00:58:03,440 --> 00:58:04,880
Then her heart will stop beating.

628
00:58:49,120 --> 00:58:52,720
Subtitles translation by:
Panuwat Baikeawon
